This is for the full size USP in .40 Caliber Left Handed Variant with Tritium Night Sights. 3 mags are included - One 12 round and Two 10 round. Manual and Case included.

I bought this forteen years ago on my 21st birthday. It is 1 inch longer than the Glock 19 that I just purchased.  This gun is extremely reliable and there nothing is wrong with it.  It has never jammed on me except once when the brass casing on a range reload was bent. Even then it fired it just didn't eject.

When I purchased it used, the gun shop owner told me it probably had about 10,000 rounds through it.  I have probably put 1000 more through it since then.  There is a little bit of wear you can see on the slide from use.

The gun is a left handed variant which means that the safety and decocker was switched to the right side of the gun.  If you are right handed, an HK armorer can switch it back inexpensively.

The coolest thing about this gun is its ambidextrous magazine release.

Here is the wikipedia article on the gun: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heckler_%26_Koch_USP
